==English==
[[Image:Suricata.suricatta.6861.jpg|thumb|150px|meerkat]]
===Etymology===
From Afrikaans ''[[meerkat#Afrikaans|meerkat]]''. The name comes from Dutch [[meerkat#Dutch|meerkat]], but by misidentification. Dutch meerkat (lit. “lake-cat”) and German ''[[Meerkatze]]'', literally “sea-cat”) are monkeys ([[guenon]]). Hindi ''[[markat]]'' (ape), Sanskrit ''[[markata]]'' is a possible origin of the name. [[Category:Articles which need Devanagari script]]

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''meerkat'''

# small [[carnivorous]] [[mammal]] of the [[mongoose]] family, from the Kalahari Desert. Scientific name: ''[[Suricata suricatta]]''

